description: Handsome Kumaki hides a burning secret. This serious salary man appears to be quite the lady-killer, but in fact, he constantly finds himself head-over-heels in love with guys – straight guys! Kumaki’s crush of the moment is on Naoto, a temperamental artist he met on his rounds as an office repairman. Will this be yet another disappointment in a never-ending series of heartbreaks? Or can Kumaki convince the doubting Naoto that true love lies within his embrace?

Straight from Hell, it's a dose of classic Hellraiser horror ripped from the pages of Marvel Comics' Hellraiser series - shipping twice this month! Re-presenting, in the mode of Doctor Who Classics, never-before-reprinted tales from some of comicdom's premiere talents! Kicking things off with one of the greatest horror artists ever: 'The Warm Red' features the work of the one-and-only Bernie Wrightson (Swamp Thing) and 'Clownin' Around' is a horror classic only Kyle Baker (Deadpool MAX) could illustrate!
name: The Warm Red; Clownin' Around

description: The horror continues with a tale of the legendary Cenobite… Face! Jan Strnad (Star Wars: Republic: Prelude To Rebellion) and Mark Chiarello (Batman/Houdini: The Devil's Workshop) reveal the origins of one of the most famous Cenobites from the classic Marvel Comics series! Cover by Kevin O'Neill (League of Extraordinary Gentlemen)!
name: The Tontine; Babycakes

description: Straight from Hell, it's another dose of classic Hellraiser horror ripped from the pages of Marvel Comics' Hellraiser series - shipping twice this month! Re-presenting, in the mode of Doctor Who Classics, never-before-reprinted tales from some of comicdom's premiere talents! This issue is three stories of grotesquery and high strangeness from John Rozum (Xombi), featuring the art of Mark Texeira (Ghost Rider) and Bo Hampton (Batman)! No other comic features these kind of sleek and intelligent horror stories told in the Hellraiser tradition! Also includes Rozum's "With My Lips," featuring art by Rod Whigham, and "Love is a Many Splendored Thing..." by Erik Saltzgaber and Mike Hoffman.
name: With My Lips; Love Is a Many Splendored Thing

description: Straight from Hell, it's classic Hellraiser horror ripped from the pages of Marvel Comics' Hellraiser series! The horror continues. Hell is on Earth, and it's illustrated by the comics legend Colleen Doran (Sandman)! This issue features both 'Later' and 'Dear Diary,' Hellraiser stories drawn by the modern master! Never before reprinted, don't miss these tales of epic and hellish proportions!
name: Later; Dear Diary; The Last Laugh

description: Straight from Hell, it's another dose of classic Hellraiser horror ripped from the pages of Marvel Comics' Hellraiser series, shipping twice this month! We kick off the epic tale of Hell's most horrific soldiers right here in "The Devil's Brigade"! Comics great Dwayne McDuffie and Paris Cullins team up for Part 1, with Ron Wolfe and John Van Fleet bringing you Part 2 of this journey into the depths of Clive Barker' twisted world!
name: Devil's Brigade Part 1 "Call to Arms"; Devil's Brigade Part 2 "The Haven On Hell Street"

description: Straight from Hell, it's another dose of classic Hellraiser horror ripped from the pages of Marvel Comics' Hellraiser series! "The Devil's Brigade" marches on! Larry Wachowski, co-writer, director, and producer of The Matrix pens Part 3 of the epic tale featuring the Cenobite squadron,"Inside the Laager" and Erik Saltzgaber and Mark Bloodworth bring you part 4, "Shoot High, Break Low." More of the intelligent horror that makes Hellraiser the masterpiece it is!
name: Devil's Brigade Part 3 "Inside The Laager"; Devil's Brigade Part 4 "Shoot High, Break Low"

description: Clive Barker's visceral visions take form in the next installment of the ongoing 'Devil's Brigade' epic. D.G. Chichester and Dwayne McDuffie team up with Denys Cowan for 'Passion,' while Nicholas Vince and Joe Barruso bring you the terrifying 'One True Faith.' No other brand of horror hooks you like Hellraiser!
name: Devil's Brigade Part 5 "Passion"; Devil's Brigade Part 6 "One True Faith"

description: It's Hell on Earth! D.G. Chichester and Dwayne McDuffie come together once again with art by Mike McMahon in the next Devil's Brigade chapter, 'Commitment,' followed by Ron Wolfe and Derek Yaniger's 'Command Performance.' Explore the depths of Clive Barker's twisted creations in these terrifying tales!
name: Devil's Brigade Part 7 "Commitment"; Devil's Brigade Part 8 "Command Performance"

description: Another bi-weekly dose of classic Hellraiser high strangeness comes your way! We have the next two epic installments of 'The Devil's Brigade,' with Erik Saltzgaber and Jackson Guice delivering 'No Loss to the Community,' followed by 'Black & White,' written by Larry Wachowski, of The Matrix fame, with art by Denys Cowan.
name: Devil's Brigade Part 9 "No Loss To the Community"; Devil's Brigade Part 10 "Black and White"

description:
Kirsti Rivers is an LA girl suddenly transplanted to the small New England town of Arkham Woods. Kirsti and her mother, Victoria, are tasked with clearing out and selling the old house left to them by Silas Scadmore, Victoria’s recently deceased eccentric uncle. In the basement of the house, Kirsti and her friends unwittingly unleash an ancient evil that could spell the end of the world—unless Kirsti can find a way to stop it!

Arkham Woods is an original stand alone manga tale of supernatural horror that draws on the Cthulhu mythos of H.P. Lovecraft.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The year is 1893. Under the iron grip of Napoleon IV, France has extended its tyrannical rule throughout the world, forging a vast Empire that rivals that of ancient Rome.

Only one man stands in defiance against the Empire, roaming at will beneath the surface of the oceans: Young Captain Nemo and his ragtag crew aboard the Nautilus II.

John Lyon, a wise-cracking, hot shot New York cop has the most amount of kills out of anyone on the force. But one day, he takes down a monstrous voodoo killer and falls victim to a terrible curse: that all the people Lyon has killed until now will come back for vengeance. Can he convince a sexy psychiatrist that he’s not nuts and erase the curse before it’s too late?

Chapter One - Chapter Seven.
name: Vol. 1
